Imaging of pancreatic and hepatic tuberculosis in an infant presenting with jaundice. The incidence of abdominal tuberculosis has increased over the last decade and can mimic any other disease. Pancreatic involvement is an uncommon cause of jaundice in children. A case of obstructive jaundice due to pancreatic tuberculosis in an infant, with hepatic involvement is reported. The sonographic and computed-tomographic features are described.